Subject: [ MDVSA-2008:087 ] - Updated policykit package
 fixes format string vulnerability


-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

 _______________________________________________________________________
 
 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDVSA-2008:087
 http://www.mandriva.com/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________
 
 Package : policykit
 Date    : April 16, 2008
 Affected: 2008.1
 _______________________________________________________________________
 
 Problem Description:
 
 A format string vulnerability in the grant helper, in PolicyKit 0.7
 and earlier, allows attackers to cause a denial of service (crash)
 and possibly execute arbitrary code via format strings in a password.
 
 The updated package has been patched to correct this issue.
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:
 
 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-1658
 _______________________________________________________________________
 
